cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CE, cs.CR, cs.IR 

The paper discusses the design of two different classes of models suitable for large-scale analysis of mortality data, a Hadoop-based ensemble of random forests trained over N-grams, and the DeepDeath, a deep classifier based on the recurrent neural network (RNN). This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of Big Data techniques and the focus on predicting health-related trajectories suggest that the paper may also belong to the Computational Epidemiology (cs.CE), Cryptography and Security (cs.CR), and Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories.
